Distribution.
Petropedetes perreti
is endemic to Cameroon . The species is found on the southern slopes of the Bamiléké Plateau, Mt. Manengouba and Mt. Nlonako (
Fig. 4
), areas which are characterized by a very high precipitation through the rainy season (
Amiet 1973
;
Herrmann et al . 2005
).
